~open Blender.
~create a new Genral file.
~remove the preexisting cube with key A(to select all) and then press X and hit enter to delete all.
~press NUM1 for front view and press Shift+A and select Mesh and then select a cube.
~Now Press  tab to enter in edit mode and then press G to move the cube(Using X,Y,Z keys to move along their respective axis).
~press S to resize the cube.
~Using Ctrl+R cut the loops into two parts.
~now select one face and using E button extrude.
~similarlly select one upper face and extrude it. then extrude another upper face and then select its 2 vertices and using G button change its position to make a shelter type shape.
~Extrude corner of the shelter and adjust them.
~Press Shift+A to add a new cube and place it on the wall and then make a window using that cube. 
~Select that window and press shift+D to make a copy of selected area  and place it another face to make a side window.
~Press Shift+A to add a new cylinder to make a pillar.
~Press Shift+A to add a new cube and place it into front to make a boundary.
~Using Extrude make comlete boundary.
color:
~select faces which have to color and then go to material properties take a new materail and then go to viewport display option to adjust the color for material then select the color   
    and click on the assign button.
~similarly fill the whole house with the color.
